===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} ''[[blak]]'', from {{OE.}} ''[[blæc]]''. Cognates include '''[[blaze]]''', '''[[bleach]]''', '''[[blond]]''', '''[[bald]]''', '''[[bale]]'', '''[[pale]]''', Latin ''[[flagare]]'', to shine, Latin ''[[blancus]]'', white, Gothic ''[[&#55296;&#57137;&#55296;&#57136;&#55296;&#57147;&#55296;&#57136;]]'' (bala), paleness, German ''[[erbleichen]]'', ''bleich'', go -, turn pale, German ''bleichen'', bleach and Russian ''[[велый]]'', white

